00:31.573 --> 00:34.064
'Dear Mr Inman,

00:34.159 --> 00:36.994
'I began by counting the days,

00:37.079 --> 00:39.748
'then the months.

00:39.832 --> 00:44.956
'I don't count on anything anymore
except the hope that you will return,

00:45.045 --> 00:50.751
'and the silent fear that in the
years since we saw each other,

00:50.843 --> 00:58.851
this war, this awful war, will have
changed us both beyond all reckoning.'

01:50.235 --> 01:52.691
This poor boy's from Alabama,

01:52.779 --> 01:55.816
He's a long way from home,
- Thank you.

02:00.245 --> 02:03.246
Why don't them Yanks just attack?

02:13.258 --> 02:15.085
Got any shirts, son?

02:15.552 --> 02:21.673
Mm-hm-hm-hm

02:21.767 --> 02:24.009
It's Mo Oakley's boy.

02:25.020 --> 02:27.938
Can't be old enough to fight, can he?

02:34.071 --> 02:36.562
Good morning,
- Morning, son.

02:37.324 --> 02:39.897
Got some boots and
jackets, You want one?

02:39.993 --> 02:42.663
Here, You want that?
- Thanks.

02:44.081 --> 02:46.536
I hope these boots can
hold up for 400 miles,

02:46.625 --> 02:49.626
'cause they're taking
me back to Cold Mountain,

02:54.591 --> 02:57.545
'I think now on the fleeting
moments betWeen us...

02:57.636 --> 03:00.209
'and wish I could repair them.

03:01.598 --> 03:05.762
My awkward nature, the
things left unsaid.'

03:10.357 --> 03:12.848
All right, that's it.

03:17.072 --> 03:19.397
Enough powder here to
blow a hole in the sky.

03:19.491 --> 03:22.860
Yeah, a real Yankee good mornin'.

03:22.953 --> 03:30.249
Mm-hm-hm-hm

03:37.384 --> 03:40.835
That old book of yours is in shreds.

03:41.972 --> 03:45.008
Same as us, Seen too much war.

03:46.477 --> 03:52.349
Hey, Oakley, Don't worry, son,
Them Yankee boys keep store hours.

03:52.441 --> 03:54.599
They ain't open yet.

04:04.328 --> 04:07.198
Close it up,

04:18.382 --> 04:21.966
Hey, where'd you come from?
- Hey, that's fresh breakfast,

04:22.053 --> 04:24.046
He's mine, Butcher,
- Hey. Hey. Get away.

04:24.139 --> 04:27.140
Hey, I saw him first,
- Come on.

04:27.226 --> 04:30.725
I saw it first.
- That's my rabbit. That's my rabbit.

04:33.607 --> 04:37.308
Get your paws off my rabbit.
Get your paws off my rabbit.

05:21.738 --> 05:24.574
'When I came with my father
to the town of Cold Mountain,

05:24.658 --> 05:27.231
'I was so shy of how I looked,

05:27.327 --> 05:29.783
'so out of place.

05:29.872 --> 05:34.201
'But did you know how happy I
was to escape from Charleston,

05:34.293 --> 05:38.041
from a world of slaves
and corsets and cotton?'

05:38.130 --> 05:40.917
What do you fools think
you'll be fightin' for?

05:41.008 --> 05:44.507
The South?
- I call this nail Northern Aggression,

05:44.595 --> 05:47.714
Damn right,
- I call this nail a Yankee Skull.

05:47.806 --> 05:50.511
Last time I checked, the
South was a direction.

05:50.601 --> 05:53.139
Never figured you for
a Lincoln lover, JT.

05:53.228 --> 05:54.972
I tell you, as soon as
I finish this chapel.

05:55.063 --> 05:57.186
I'm gonna go off and
kill me some Yankees.

05:57.274 --> 05:58.519
Piss and vinegar.

05:58.609 --> 06:01.230
Fightin' for a rich
man's slave, that's what.

06:01.320 --> 06:02.897
Whoa, here comes the minister.

06:02.988 --> 06:05.693
Ben, thank you, Will
you assist my daughter?

06:05.782 --> 06:07.740
Lord have mercy, look at that bonnet.

06:07.826 --> 06:09.534
Look what's in it.

06:09.620 --> 06:11.493
Oakley, hand me the hammer, boy.

06:11.580 --> 06:13.619
That's a true Southern belle,

06:13.707 --> 06:18.618
Mr Swanger. Good morning to you,
- Morning, Reverend.

06:18.712 --> 06:21.796
Esco, you remember my daughter, Ada,

06:21.882 --> 06:24.040
Miss Monroe,
- Good morning,

06:24.134 --> 06:25.297
Morning,
- Morning,

06:25.385 --> 06:27.212
Excellent progress,
- Morning,

06:27.304 --> 06:29.973
Mrs Swanger, Mrs Castlereagh,
- Morning, Reverend.

06:30.057 --> 06:32.263
Now, if y'all will excuse me.

06:32.351 --> 06:37.096
In Charleston, my congregation would
still be disputing the size of the windows.

06:37.189 --> 06:38.220
It's a chapel.

06:38.315 --> 06:41.269
Miss Monroe, I was
just thinkin' about you.

06:41.360 --> 06:45.025
Cold Mountain must feel
like the end of the world.

06:45.113 --> 06:47.687
Not at all,

06:47.783 --> 06:52.445
It's very beautiful,
- Well, you put us all to shame.

06:52.538 --> 06:55.373
Men up here had a bearing on
what they thought a woman was,

06:55.457 --> 06:58.826
and then you showed up,
- Oh,,,

06:58.919 --> 07:01.327
No, I doubt that,
- Oh, believe me.

07:01.421 --> 07:06.333
If you was to say a word to one of these
fools, I could get my top field cleared,

07:07.845 --> 07:10.300
Any one?
- No, um,,.

07:11.098 --> 07:13.423
Him in particular.

07:13.517 --> 07:15.593
Up in the rafters.

07:15.686 --> 07:18.307
Won't normally say boo to a goose.

07:21.400 --> 07:25.184
He's been pressin' me since
the day you arrived here,

07:29.158 --> 07:32.361
Your top field cleared?
- That's right.

07:37.040 --> 07:40.540
Good morning, I'm Ada Monroe.

07:41.503 --> 07:43.295
Inman.

07:43.380 --> 07:44.578
Inman.

07:44.673 --> 07:46.500
WP Inman.

07:48.177 --> 07:49.587
WP Inman.

07:49.678 --> 07:52.383
Repeatin' a thing doesn't improve it.

07:54.266 --> 07:56.887
People call me Inman.

07:59.104 --> 08:01.097
How 'bout that? Inman speaks.

08:01.190 --> 08:05.139
If you were to take a glass of cider,
your friends might stop staring.

08:07.821 --> 08:09.695
Inman.

08:11.283 --> 08:16.324
You're just jealous, I'm gonna take
her for a walk at Bishop's Creek,

08:16.413 --> 08:19.165
Billy, is this frame flush?
- Thank you.

08:19.249 --> 08:23.033
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
Thank you, yeah, right.

08:23.795 --> 08:26.962
Richie, I seen your house, There
ain't a square angle anywhere near it.

08:27.049 --> 08:29.291
And what do you do?

08:29.384 --> 08:31.673
I work wood.

08:31.762 --> 08:33.589
Hunt.

08:34.597 --> 08:37.171
Mostly work wood.

08:39.394 --> 08:41.433
Clear fields?

08:45.609 --> 08:47.981
I can clear a field.

08:49.154 --> 08:52.855
Was there something in particular
you wished to say to me?

08:57.454 --> 09:00.289
Not that comes to me.

09:06.421 --> 09:09.292
I'll say thank you,,, for the cider.

09:16.723 --> 09:18.550
You'll walk unscathed...

09:23.814 --> 09:29.983
No ploughman's blade
will cut thee down

09:31.822 --> 09:38.359
No cutler's horn will mark thy face

09:38.453 --> 09:45.251
I've gone to find my ain true love

09:45.335 --> 09:52.501
I've gone to find my ain true love

10:59.284 --> 11:02.285
Move back. Go back. Move back.

11:02.371 --> 11:05.040
Go back. Go back.

11:05.123 --> 11:09.702
They're trapped in the wrong damn
crater, Whole plan backfired on 'em.

11:09.795 --> 11:12.202
Send them Yanks straight to hell,

11:12.297 --> 11:15.417
Hold it, hold it,
- Let's go, Turn it around.

11:17.678 --> 11:20.548
Damn fools dug their own grave.

11:20.639 --> 11:23.426
We've got 'em now, boys,

11:25.060 --> 11:28.678
It's a turkey shoot,
- What?

11:28.772 --> 11:32.141
It's a turkey shoot, They've
run themselves into a hole.

11:32.234 --> 11:34.310
Hell's busted.

12:35.756 --> 12:37.795
Oakley.

12:49.853 --> 12:52.724
Oakley.

12:59.112 --> 13:01.271
Oakley.

13:27.266 --> 13:30.682
Inman. Inman.
- Oakley.

13:33.939 --> 13:35.647
Oakley.

14:03.385 --> 14:05.627
Inman.
- Come on.

14:06.972 --> 14:08.680
Inman.

14:11.268 --> 14:14.222
I've got you.

14:41.298 --> 14:43.871
I got a few,

14:43.967 --> 14:46.458
You saw?
- I saw.

14:50.724 --> 14:53.262
Am I gonna die?

14:56.021 --> 14:58.808
Your folks can be real proud of you.

15:12.246 --> 15:17.038
Son, this fellow says he'll
play whatever you want.

15:19.211 --> 15:22.995
What about 'Bonaparte's
Retreat'? That's one I play.

15:28.220 --> 15:31.589
No, Play me somethin' sweet.

15:31.682 --> 15:34.303
Like a girl's waiting for me,

15:35.519 --> 15:39.469
You heard him,
- I only know a couple of tunes.

15:39.565 --> 15:42.103
Like when you're at Bishop's Creek,,,

15:42.901 --> 15:45.819
and you're thirsty,,,

15:45.904 --> 15:48.822
and the water's so cool.

15:50.534 --> 15:52.692
I don't know what music that is.

16:18.145 --> 16:21.229
I'm reachin' Cold Mountain before you.

16:58.477 --> 17:00.434
Good morning, Sally,

17:05.067 --> 17:08.352
Well, that's a
fine-sounding thing, - Oh,,.

17:09.363 --> 17:11.355
My piano.

17:12.907 --> 17:14.983
Oh, I've been missing it.

17:15.077 --> 17:19.868
Thank you, by the way, Inman's
in my top field clearing his debt.

17:19.957 --> 17:21.949
Oh, dear.

17:25.838 --> 17:28.126
And then he had nothing to say.

17:28.214 --> 17:30.753
He was happy.

17:32.052 --> 17:34.424
Really?

17:34.513 --> 17:37.430
Are men so different in Charleston?

17:39.393 --> 17:41.136
Men?

17:42.563 --> 17:44.472
I don't know.

17:44.565 --> 17:50.270
If you're sayin' you might like him,
why not go over and say good mornin'?

17:50.362 --> 17:52.355
I should be gettin' along.

17:52.447 --> 17:55.318
Walk on, quickly.

17:55.409 --> 17:58.529
Come on, Walk on, Slowly.

17:58.620 --> 18:00.660
Walk on.

18:10.716 --> 18:13.171
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

18:45.000 --> 18:47.573
My dear daughter, Ada,

18:47.669 --> 18:54.206
who's given up so much for so long to help
me in my ministry, and upon whom I rely.

18:56.804 --> 19:03.091
Friends, we are both very happy to
have this opportunity tonight,,,

19:04.269 --> 19:07.187
to thank you from our hearts,,,

19:08.232 --> 19:13.309
for your kind welcome and,
most of all, such a fine chapel.

19:14.863 --> 19:17.188
So,,,

19:17.282 --> 19:20.283
,, thank you, and God bless you.

19:23.330 --> 19:29.499
Our house is always open
to any of you at any time.

19:29.586 --> 19:32.042
Welcome.

19:32.130 --> 19:33.210
Esco?

19:37.511 --> 19:39.503
That gentleman
- he help build the chapel?

19:39.596 --> 19:42.550
Him? No, that's Teague.

19:42.641 --> 19:46.508
At one time the Teague family
owned the whole of Cold Mountain.

19:46.603 --> 19:51.099
My farm, your farm, it all
belonged to his grandpappy.

19:51.191 --> 19:53.765
Teague wanted this place
bad, and you got it.

19:53.861 --> 19:56.612
And he's here sniffin'
out an advantage.

19:58.657 --> 20:04.280
There's no advantage here, except
to celebrate a job well done.

20:04.371 --> 20:06.577
And that is a good thing
in these troubled times,

20:06.665 --> 20:09.749
Miss Monroe,
- Thank you,

20:14.506 --> 20:19.382
Were you never planning to come inside?
- I'm wetter than a fish,

20:20.846 --> 20:24.049
There's a good fire going,
- I'm all right.

20:26.810 --> 20:29.681
You're always carrying a tray.

20:31.982 --> 20:35.565
I was going to take some
root beer over to the Negroes.

20:43.619 --> 20:46.536
Somebody said you were enlisting,

20:46.663 --> 20:50.412
Are you?
- If there is a war, we'll all fight,

21:04.139 --> 21:07.473
Did you get a picture made?
- Say again?

21:07.559 --> 21:12.055
A tintype, with your musket
and your courage on display.

21:13.398 --> 21:15.936
You're laughin' at me.

21:17.444 --> 21:19.816
I don't know you.

21:23.617 --> 21:26.903
This doesn't come out right.

21:26.995 --> 21:32.535
If it were enough just to
stand, without the words,,.

21:34.336 --> 21:36.329
It is.

21:39.341 --> 21:41.215
It is.

21:44.930 --> 21:47.136
You,,, Look.

21:47.224 --> 21:50.640
Look, Look at the sky
now, What colour is it?

21:52.813 --> 21:55.730
Or the way,,, a hawk flies?

21:58.360 --> 22:01.231
Or you wake up,,,

22:01.321 --> 22:05.818
and your ribs are bruised
thinking so hard on somebody.

22:06.910 --> 22:09.532
What do you call that?

22:18.005 --> 22:20.081
I'll do that.

22:21.300 --> 22:24.135
I can't get much wetter,

22:26.555 --> 22:30.932
'What if you are killed,
and I'll never see you again?

22:31.018 --> 22:35.810
'You said after a few years I
would barely remember your name.

22:35.898 --> 22:38.436
'Oh, Inman.

22:38.525 --> 22:43.234
It is more than three years,
and I remember your name.'

22:44.323 --> 22:47.110
Soldiers, Don't get up.

22:49.077 --> 22:51.284
You are mentioned
tonight in my report.

22:51.371 --> 22:56.247
You men from Cold Mountain have
once again been heroes for the cause.

22:56.335 --> 23:00.202
There are Yankees in that stand of trees
between us, stuck there from the retreat.

23:00.297 --> 23:05.588
If they stay there, tomorrow mornin'
they can shoot us down for sport.

23:09.264 --> 23:11.838
Go around.

23:13.811 --> 23:15.269
It's a Reb.

23:15.354 --> 23:17.014
How many of them are there?

23:17.105 --> 23:18.516
I think there's five.

23:18.607 --> 23:21.561
Under the trees,

23:23.403 --> 23:25.526
We got 'em,
- Let's go, let's go.

23:25.614 --> 23:27.737
Butcher's down.

23:28.909 --> 23:32.242
Leave him, leave him,
He's gone, Let's go.

23:34.957 --> 23:37.626
Go, go. Go. Run.

23:38.961 --> 23:42.709
Go. Go. Go.
- Hold your fire.

23:42.798 --> 23:45.040
What's over by them trees?

23:45.133 --> 23:47.671
It's us. It's us.

23:49.888 --> 23:52.260
I said hold your fire. Hold your fire.

23:59.565 --> 24:02.815
Leave him, Leave him.

24:02.901 --> 24:05.227
Agh.

24:32.181 --> 24:35.051
Inman'll get it.

24:35.142 --> 24:39.436
Supposed to bring good luck,
a bird caught in a room.

24:39.521 --> 24:44.064
I'm so sorry to have kept you
waiting, She'll just be a few seconds,

25:48.924 --> 25:50.963
Mr Inman,
- Reverend,

25:51.051 --> 25:53.886
What can I do for you?
- I have some sheet music.

25:53.971 --> 25:57.422
It belonged to my
father, No use to me.

25:57.516 --> 25:59.176
Thank you,

25:59.268 --> 26:01.640
You must come in,
- I should probably get along.

26:01.728 --> 26:04.932
Mr Inman is more comfortable outdoors.

26:05.023 --> 26:08.724
Perhaps we might,,,
perhaps we might take a walk.

26:08.819 --> 26:10.895
A splendid idea.

26:13.657 --> 26:16.195
Let me just get your hat.

26:19.746 --> 26:24.492
I dragged my poor daughter 400 miles
from Charleston to Cold Mountain...

26:24.585 --> 26:28.914
because my doctors, they've
been sayin' my chest is weak.

26:29.006 --> 26:31.793
So the air's supposed to do me good.

26:32.801 --> 26:35.126
But it's the view I think heals.

26:35.220 --> 26:39.847
It's what people say we're
fightin' for, To keep it that way.

26:39.933 --> 26:43.931
I have no plans to preach
war in my church, Mr Inman.

26:45.439 --> 26:51.109
I imagine God is weary of being called
down on both sides of an argument.

26:53.322 --> 26:55.813
I imagine God is.

27:01.747 --> 27:03.905
Thank you.

27:05.417 --> 27:08.288
Now, your father played
the piano, did he?

27:08.378 --> 27:10.620
That's right, He was a teacher.

27:10.714 --> 27:13.122
And is your father living, Mr Inman?

27:13.217 --> 27:15.458
He is not,
- And your mother?

27:15.552 --> 27:18.838
No, sir, She died when I was born.

27:46.583 --> 27:49.205
Farewell, vain world

27:49.294 --> 27:51.287
I'm going home

27:51.380 --> 27:55.543
My saviour smiles and bids me come

27:55.634 --> 27:59.169
And I don't care to stay here long

27:59.263 --> 28:04.008
Sweet angels beckon me away

28:04.101 --> 28:08.264
To sing God's praise in endless day

28:08.355 --> 28:11.689
And I don't care to stay here long

28:11.775 --> 28:15.476
Right up yonder, Christians...

28:15.571 --> 28:19.189
Secession,
- North Carolina left the Union.

28:19.283 --> 28:25.286
O, yes, my Lord, for I
don't care to stay here long

28:25.372 --> 28:26.451
Whoo.

28:26.540 --> 28:28.995
We got our
war. - Whoo-hoo.

28:29.084 --> 28:31.540
...that I am born to die

28:31.628 --> 28:36.290
From grief and woe my soul shall fly

28:36.383 --> 28:39.717
And I don't care to stay here long

28:39.803 --> 28:44.880
Bright angels shall convey me home

28:44.975 --> 28:49.187
Away to New Jerusalem

28:49.271 --> 28:54.645
And I don't care to stay here long

28:56.069 --> 29:00.815
We got our war. We got it.
We got it. It's about time.

29:00.908 --> 29:02.900
Whoo.

29:04.953 --> 29:07.444
All right.
- Inman. Inman.

29:07.539 --> 29:10.030
Ready to fight, son, ready to fight.

29:10.125 --> 29:11.204
Whoo.

29:11.293 --> 29:13.665
We got our war, man.

29:13.754 --> 29:16.245
Well, you have your war.

29:17.424 --> 29:18.587
Ada.

29:19.593 --> 29:21.420
Ada.

29:22.596 --> 29:25.513
It's a great day for North Carolina.

29:25.599 --> 29:29.644
Those who follow Lincoln
or preach abolition,,,

29:30.479 --> 29:32.637
you best keep one eye
open when you're sleepin'.

29:32.731 --> 29:35.934
OI' boogeyman might get you.

29:36.026 --> 29:39.312
Are you the law all
of a sudden, Mr Teague?

29:39.404 --> 29:41.563
That's right, son.

29:41.657 --> 29:45.701
Home Guard for Haywood County,
And I'm the law from today.

29:45.786 --> 29:50.614
Y'all go fight now, We'll
watch over your sweethearts.

29:50.707 --> 29:53.033
Hey, Teague, Why ain't you fightin'?

29:53.126 --> 29:55.748
'Cause he's too old.

29:55.838 --> 29:57.996
Yeah.

29:58.090 --> 29:59.964
Whoo.

30:00.884 --> 30:03.802
You might be safer back in Charleston,

30:07.766 --> 30:12.013
But then who'll be waiting for you?
- Three cheers for North Carolina.

30:12.104 --> 30:14.227
All right,
- Three cheers for the South.

30:14.314 --> 30:15.892
Hip hip hurrah.

30:15.983 --> 30:18.189
Hip hip hurrah.

30:18.277 --> 30:20.400
Hip hip hurrah.

30:32.124 --> 30:34.959
Inman, It belongs to Inman.

30:35.043 --> 30:37.369
I got it, He's here.

30:41.675 --> 30:45.720
They found that book you
been worryin' about, soldier.

31:26.303 --> 31:28.212
Wait.

31:38.023 --> 31:41.855
I found you this
book to take with you.

31:41.944 --> 31:44.020
William Bartram.

31:45.447 --> 31:47.772
They tell me it's good.

31:48.909 --> 31:52.859
I think he writes about
these parts, the author, so,,.

31:54.122 --> 31:56.245
Thank you.

31:57.584 --> 31:59.743
And this.

32:07.886 --> 32:10.591
I'm not smiling in it.

32:13.183 --> 32:16.018
I don't know how to do that,

32:16.103 --> 32:18.012
hold a smile,

32:41.587 --> 32:43.579
Ada,
- What?

33:06.403 --> 33:08.894
Whoa.
- He'll be back in a month.

33:11.492 --> 33:13.899
Kiss her for me.

33:21.293 --> 33:23.416
Come on, let's go.

33:28.550 --> 33:31.468
I'll be waiting for you.

34:06.839 --> 34:08.463
Lookin' good, Butcher.

34:08.549 --> 34:11.040
Bring home some
Yankee scalps, Swimmer.

34:11.134 --> 34:12.960
Yee-haw.

34:17.431 --> 34:22.592
Look out the window, ladies. See
what these poor fools are dyin' for.

34:22.688 --> 34:26.851
How many would still lose a
leg for the rich man's slave?

34:27.693 --> 34:33.280
Most of these soldiers'll be dead by
morning, or if they're stubborn, by nightfall.

34:33.364 --> 34:38.027
I've other men outside in the
courtyard waitin' for beds,

34:38.120 --> 34:40.741
so any kind word will be a blessin'.

34:44.168 --> 34:46.741
It's the heat, I'm sorry, They rot.

34:46.837 --> 34:49.375
Pigeon River,,.

34:49.464 --> 34:52.134
How are you, son?

34:52.217 --> 34:55.217
Cold,,, Mountain,,.

34:57.598 --> 34:59.923
I- I'm sorry,

35:00.017 --> 35:04.429
You want water?
- Cold,,, Mountain.

35:06.315 --> 35:08.391
Cold Mountain?

35:09.318 --> 35:11.310
Cold Mountain.

35:14.656 --> 35:20.529
Do you worry when there's no
word from him? From Mr Inman?

35:22.247 --> 35:24.074
Yes.

35:26.335 --> 35:29.039
But then I've tried countin'
the number of words...

35:29.129 --> 35:34.005
which have passed between Mr Inman and me
- not very many.

35:34.092 --> 35:38.339
But I think about him,
Daddy, all the time.

35:38.430 --> 35:42.642
I lost your mother after
22 months of marriage.

35:44.603 --> 35:47.094
It was enough to fill a life.

35:53.195 --> 35:55.318
That was the last of the ham,

35:55.405 --> 35:58.821
It was delicious,
- I have to learn how to cook.

35:58.909 --> 36:01.317
I was thinking of saying
something in chapel.

36:01.411 --> 36:03.534
Perhaps some of the
womenfolk will volunteer.

36:03.622 --> 36:06.825
I can't have people coming
here and cooking for me.

36:08.794 --> 36:10.205
I so,,.

36:10.295 --> 36:11.837
I so regret,,.

36:11.922 --> 36:18.209
I should have raised you less like a
companion and more like a young woman.

36:18.303 --> 36:22.431
I'm sorry, Ada, And
for dragging you here.

36:22.516 --> 36:24.555
I'm not sorry.

36:27.771 --> 36:30.476
I would have followed you anywhere,

36:32.985 --> 36:35.654
To Mongolia,
- Mongolia.

36:36.780 --> 36:41.987
But with no one left to work this place,
nothing to buy, nothing left to buy it with.

36:43.620 --> 36:47.665
I just don't know how we're
gonna get through another winter.

36:50.377 --> 36:56.131
Will you play me somethin'? Somethin'
peaceful while I look over my sermon.

36:56.216 --> 36:58.256
It's too damp out here,
You should come inside.

36:58.343 --> 37:00.170
No.

37:00.262 --> 37:01.293
I like it.

37:16.987 --> 37:19.988
Daddy, bring the tablecloth in.

37:22.576 --> 37:25.067
Come inside before you drown.

38:12.793 --> 38:14.999
You have a letter.

38:15.087 --> 38:17.126
North Carolina.

38:18.882 --> 38:21.456
It's come a long way.

38:24.346 --> 38:26.635
It's not too recent.

38:26.723 --> 38:29.214
It's written this past winter.

38:31.478 --> 38:33.886
I'm afraid I can't read who it's from,

38:38.735 --> 38:40.894
'Dear Mr Inman,,,'

38:41.864 --> 38:47.487
'Since you've left, time has been
measured out in bitter chapters.

38:47.578 --> 38:50.247
'Last fall, my poor father died.

38:52.207 --> 38:55.078
'Our farm at Black Cove is abandoned.

38:58.005 --> 39:02.216
'Every house in these
mountains touched by tragedy.

39:04.595 --> 39:09.340
'Each day the dread... of
learning who has fallen...

39:10.601 --> 39:13.602
who will not return
from this terrible war.

39:15.606 --> 39:18.642
'And no word from you.

39:18.734 --> 39:20.773
'Are you alive?

39:20.861 --> 39:23.613
'I pray to God you are.

39:24.781 --> 39:27.070
'This war is lost
on the battlefield...

39:27.159 --> 39:31.951
and is being lost tWice over
by those who stayed behind.'

39:32.039 --> 39:35.408
He ain't comin' back, you know that.

39:39.588 --> 39:42.293
You must know that in your heart.

39:44.885 --> 39:47.008
Look at me.

39:48.764 --> 39:51.136
Look at me.

39:55.854 --> 39:58.428
I'm not nothin',

40:00.734 --> 40:05.277
'I'm still waiting,
as I promised I would.

40:07.783 --> 40:11.318
'But I find myself alone
and at the end of my wits...

40:12.996 --> 40:17.705
too embarrassed to keep taking from
those who can least afford to give.'

40:18.794 --> 40:21.748
Ada. It's Sally.

40:21.839 --> 40:23.037
Ada.

40:23.131 --> 40:25.254
Look at the state of this place.

40:25.342 --> 40:29.007
Well, set it on the porch.

40:30.514 --> 40:33.965
She let them slaves
go free, and now,,.

40:34.059 --> 40:38.851
Poor soul, she's got nobody and
nothin', and waitin' on a ghost.

40:45.237 --> 40:47.111
Shoo.

40:49.741 --> 40:51.651
Go away.

40:56.707 --> 40:58.035
Devil.

41:01.712 --> 41:06.208
'My last thread of courage now
is to put my faith in you...

41:08.677 --> 41:11.429
'and to believe I will see you again.

41:12.598 --> 41:17.058
'So now I say to
you, plain as I can...

41:18.520 --> 41:21.770
'if you are fighting, stop fighting.

41:23.025 --> 41:26.358
'If you are marching, stop marching.

41:28.489 --> 41:30.896
'Come back to me.

41:34.453 --> 41:36.778
Come back to me is my request,'

41:44.963 --> 41:47.454
'Come back to me.

41:49.092 --> 41:52.758
Come back to me is my request.'

41:54.973 --> 41:58.923
Wounded men, don't stray
from the hospital grounds.

41:59.603 --> 42:01.643
Hey.

42:03.398 --> 42:05.023
If they send us back to fight,,.

42:05.108 --> 42:09.023
Hey, get your peanuts
now, from the blind man,

42:10.447 --> 42:13.863
Hey, your hot goobers here,
- It's a sad day.

42:17.871 --> 42:20.706
Gettin' better, soldier?

42:20.791 --> 42:23.496
Seems that way.

42:23.585 --> 42:25.542
I wouldn't hurry.

42:25.629 --> 42:29.543
The war's almost done, Don't
need your help to lose it.

42:30.801 --> 42:35.926
You got ten minutes now, boys, Ten
minutes to get your haircuts and shaves.

42:36.014 --> 42:38.885
I've been meanin' to ask you,
Where'd you take your wound?

42:38.976 --> 42:41.217
Oh, before I was born.

42:41.311 --> 42:43.719
Never set eyes on a
thing in this world.

42:43.814 --> 42:49.401
Not a tree, a gun or a woman,
Put my hand on all three, though,

42:51.113 --> 42:53.948
What would you give for that?
- Hm?

42:54.032 --> 42:58.410
To have your eyeballs for ten minutes,
- Ten minutes?

42:58.495 --> 43:01.033
I wouldn't give an Indian head cent,

43:01.123 --> 43:05.251
Might turn me hateful,
- That's sure what seein's done to me.

43:05.335 --> 43:08.253
No, that's not the way I meant it.

43:08.338 --> 43:10.829
You said ten minutes.

43:10.924 --> 43:15.337
It's havin' a thing and then
the loss of it I'm talking about.

43:15.429 --> 43:21.134
Then we don't agree, There's not much I
wouldn't give for ten minutes of someplace.

43:21.226 --> 43:25.176
Yeah, someplace,,, or someone.

43:28.233 --> 43:31.234
You watch yourself, now.

43:31.320 --> 43:34.321
They're shootin' men who
take themselves a walk.

44:13.237 --> 44:16.356
By order of Zebulon Vance,

44:16.448 --> 44:19.864
governor of this great
state of North Carolina,

44:19.952 --> 44:24.993
any soldier turned deserter
is guilty of treason,

44:25.082 --> 44:27.917
and should be hunted down like a dog.

44:29.419 --> 44:34.758
Any man who takes in a deserter
is likewise guilty of treason.

44:34.842 --> 44:38.756
The Home Guard is powered to
enter any place it sees fit...

44:38.846 --> 44:42.215
without notice or constraint

44:42.307 --> 44:45.095
Captain Teague needs more volunteers.

44:45.185 --> 44:49.432
Any man whose age or infirmity prevents
him from fightin' shall join us...

44:49.523 --> 44:54.066
to protect this county from Yankee
raiders and traitors to the cause,

44:54.153 --> 44:56.062
Is there a letter for me?
- Nothin'.

44:56.155 --> 45:00.947
We've been gettin' no post through at all,
The sooner we lose this war the better.

45:01.034 --> 45:04.201
They say not one boy in ten is
comin' home to these mountains.

45:04.288 --> 45:09.578
Teague and his rabble throwin' their weight
around, They're worse than the Yankees.

45:09.668 --> 45:12.159
Might I speak with you, please?

45:13.755 --> 45:16.591
This was the Reverend Monroe's.

45:19.052 --> 45:21.674
I don't know who would want a watch.

45:24.099 --> 45:26.637
Who can bear to look at the time?

45:29.688 --> 45:32.724
I've got a little
salt pork you can have.

45:34.234 --> 45:37.105
Keep your daddy's watch.

45:38.572 --> 45:41.145
Thank you.

45:42.743 --> 45:44.700
I was talkin' to some
of the other womenfolk...

45:44.786 --> 45:47.360
about maybe lookin' in on you at
Black Cove, It's hard right now, but,,.

45:47.456 --> 45:51.288
Oh, no, I manage very
well, whatever the talk is.

45:53.754 --> 45:56.327
I'm very grateful for the pork.

45:58.634 --> 46:01.753
Which I intend to pay for, of course.

46:10.354 --> 46:13.105
Is everything all right?

46:13.190 --> 46:15.313
Mm-hmm.

46:29.623 --> 46:31.450
Ada.

46:31.542 --> 46:33.368
Ada.

46:35.337 --> 46:38.872
Why, Ada, you are skinny
as a whippet, girl,

46:38.966 --> 46:42.417
You are comin' indoors with me,
- No, I can't.

46:42.511 --> 46:44.503
I don't,,.

46:45.681 --> 46:47.839
I can't keep countin'
on your kindness.

46:47.933 --> 46:50.009
Now, come on, I'm makin' a stew.

46:50.102 --> 46:54.930
We'd be proud to have you, Esco's
gonna be wantin' his dinner.

46:56.233 --> 46:59.732
I just wanna stop, I tell you, Yeah.

46:59.820 --> 47:04.233
Sit on the porch with Sal,
watch my boys in the fields,

47:04.324 --> 47:08.239
holler 'Good job' every hour or so.

47:08.328 --> 47:12.112
That'll be a good day,
when our boys get home.

47:12.207 --> 47:15.042
What about your people in Charleston?

47:18.172 --> 47:20.923
There are no people.

47:21.008 --> 47:23.759
And there's no money.

47:23.844 --> 47:27.794
My father had some
bonds and investments.

47:27.890 --> 47:31.590
They're worthless now,
of course, The war,,.

47:33.187 --> 47:38.098
They're not worth anything, I
don't have anywhere else to go.

47:43.739 --> 47:45.945
I don't wanna go,

47:48.118 --> 47:51.036
You're waiting on a feller,
- Oh.

47:54.208 --> 47:56.284
Look down our well,,,
- Esco,,.

47:56.376 --> 47:58.369
She should.

47:59.129 --> 48:04.420
If you look down our well with a mirror,
you'll see the future, It's what they say.

48:05.969 --> 48:08.721
You do it, She does it.

48:11.058 --> 48:12.718
What kind of mirror?

48:14.019 --> 48:17.637
We'll hold on to you, Esco, you hold on,
- I got her,

48:17.731 --> 48:20.305
We got you,
- Mm.

48:21.902 --> 48:23.895
See anything?

48:26.198 --> 48:27.361
Uh,,.

48:28.158 --> 48:29.652
Uh,,,

48:29.743 --> 48:32.661
I don't know,
- I tried many a time,

48:32.746 --> 48:36.115
lookin' for a sign my
boys were comin' home.

48:36.208 --> 48:38.497
I never saw a dickey bird,

48:53.600 --> 48:56.471
Oh.
- Are you all right? Ada?

48:56.562 --> 48:59.313
What? What happened?

49:01.358 --> 49:04.193
What'd you see? What'd you see?

49:05.028 --> 49:08.362
'Yesterday, I saw you
walkin' back to me...

49:09.199 --> 49:11.275
'or thought I did.

49:12.494 --> 49:17.073
'I found myself crouching
over Sally Swanger's well...

49:22.504 --> 49:25.956
'...like a madwoman
staring into its secrets.

49:27.843 --> 49:33.383
'Was it you I saw walking home
to me, or was it your ghost?

49:33.474 --> 49:37.685
'After so long, I know I must
learn to survive on my own...

49:37.769 --> 49:40.889
'and accept you will not return.

49:40.981 --> 49:44.315
And yet I cannot. I cannot.'

49:49.990 --> 49:52.148
Them cows wants milkin'.

49:52.242 --> 49:55.492
If that letter ain't urgent,
them cows is is what I'm sayin'.

49:55.579 --> 49:57.618
I don't know you.

49:57.706 --> 50:00.873
Old lady Swanger says you need help.

50:00.959 --> 50:03.035
Here I am.

50:03.921 --> 50:08.796
I,,, I need help but,,, I need,,, I
do need help, but I need a labourer.

50:08.884 --> 50:13.925
There's,,, ploughing and rough work, I
think there's been a misunderstanding.

50:14.014 --> 50:16.849
What's that rake for?

50:16.934 --> 50:19.685
The rake?  - Well, it ain't 
for gardenin', that's for sure.

50:19.770 --> 50:23.388
Number one, you got a horse? I
can plough all day, I'm a worker.

50:23.482 --> 50:25.889
Number two, ain't no man better'n me,

50:25.984 --> 50:30.231
'cause there ain't no man around
who ain't old or full of mischief,

50:31.657 --> 50:35.191
I know your plight,
- My plight?

50:35.285 --> 50:38.820
Am I hard to hear? 'Cause
you keep repeatin' everything.

50:38.914 --> 50:42.579
I ain't lookin' for money, I never cared
for it and now it ain't worth nothin'.

50:42.668 --> 50:45.834
I expect to board and
eat, at the same table,

50:45.921 --> 50:49.088
I ain't a servant, if you get my meanin',
- You're not a servant.

50:49.174 --> 50:53.836
People's gonna have to empty
their own night jars is my point.

50:53.929 --> 50:56.800
And I don't expect to work whilst
you sit around and watch, neither.

50:56.890 --> 50:58.005
Right.

50:58.100 --> 51:00.935
Right, Is that a yes or a no?

51:03.564 --> 51:06.600
There's a rooster, He's
the devil, I'm sure of it.

51:06.692 --> 51:09.265
I go near him and he
is at me with his spurs.

51:09.361 --> 51:11.519
He's Lucifer himself.

51:11.613 --> 51:14.863
I despise a floggin' rooster.

51:15.826 --> 51:17.865
Oh, no, I wouldn't,,.

51:17.953 --> 51:20.954
My name's Ruby Thewes,
I know your name.

51:30.382 --> 51:32.873
Let's put him in a pot.

51:39.141 --> 51:40.968
Mm-hm-hm-hm

51:41.059 --> 51:44.974
Mm-hm-hm-hm

51:46.815 --> 51:48.274
Mm-hm-hm-hm

51:48.358 --> 51:52.688
Mm-hm-hm-hm

51:58.827 --> 52:00.736
Urgh.

52:01.788 --> 52:04.326
Mm-hm-hm-hm-hm-hm

52:04.416 --> 52:08.081
Mm-hm-hm-hm-hm

52:09.671 --> 52:15.460
I've gone to find my ain true love

52:36.114 --> 52:40.361
You're my angel, my butterfly.

52:41.912 --> 52:44.237
Come fly away.

52:47.125 --> 52:50.043
My love,,.

52:50.128 --> 52:53.082
God forgive me for doin' this.

52:53.173 --> 52:55.462
I'm so sorry.

52:55.551 --> 52:58.302
I'm sendin' you to a better place.

53:00.305 --> 53:03.176
You go fly away.

53:03.267 --> 53:05.093
Hey.

53:05.185 --> 53:10.227
Don't do that.  - Don't pull 
that trigger, I'm a man of God,

53:10.315 --> 53:14.812
I killed several of them,
- I mean I'm God's minister.

53:14.903 --> 53:18.948
What part of God's business is
throwin' a woman down a gorge?

53:19.032 --> 53:21.274
A slave woman.

53:21.368 --> 53:25.152
Can you see that in this
light? Black as a bucket of tar,

53:25.247 --> 53:28.164
Is she dead?
- No, I drugged her,

53:28.250 --> 53:30.492
like you would a butterfly.

53:30.586 --> 53:33.587
And I care for her, That's
the heartbreak of it.

53:34.381 --> 53:37.299
She's got my bastard in her belly.

53:37.384 --> 53:39.792
Come on, Back up,

53:42.055 --> 53:44.546
I'm beggin' you,
- Git.

53:44.641 --> 53:50.312
It's better you blow out my brains
than return me to this place.

53:51.231 --> 53:54.185
You're gonna put her
back where she sleeps.

53:55.402 --> 53:58.569
I do that, the members
will lynch me...

53:58.655 --> 54:03.282
for sirin' a bastard while servin' as
their preacher, We're a strict congregation.

54:03.368 --> 54:06.987
We've churched men for pickin'
up a fiddle on the Sabbath.

54:07.080 --> 54:09.916
So you reckon to kill her?
What, because she's a slave?

54:12.544 --> 54:14.252
I,,, um,,.

54:14.338 --> 54:16.663
There's a back door, Have pity.

54:19.009 --> 54:21.167
Thank you.

54:21.261 --> 54:23.966
I was gonna do a grievous wrong.

54:26.642 --> 54:29.559
I think I should go
back up to my wife.

54:31.146 --> 54:33.222
She wakes at the slightest noise.

54:33.315 --> 54:35.189
Agh. Ohh,,.

54:35.275 --> 54:37.268
Where's some paper and a pencil?

54:47.955 --> 54:51.655
Hey, Ada. You up?

54:53.794 --> 54:55.122
Yes.

54:55.212 --> 54:57.703
Wha,,,? It's still dark.

54:57.798 --> 55:00.668
Tell that to the cows, It's late.

55:07.432 --> 55:09.721
You all set?

55:09.810 --> 55:11.886
Oh, I-I just have to eat somethin'.

55:11.979 --> 55:14.896
Well, then, you got to get
up earlier, What's that?

55:16.900 --> 55:19.189
A novel.

55:19.278 --> 55:22.777
You wanna carry a book,
carry one you can write in.

55:24.116 --> 55:30.450
We got our own story, It's called
Black Cove Farm: Catastrophe.

55:31.415 --> 55:35.875
I can spell it, too, Learned it the
same place you did, in the schoolhouse.

55:35.961 --> 55:38.499
One of the first words they taught me,

55:38.589 --> 55:43.879
'Ruby Thewes, you are a
c- a-t-a-s-t-r-o-p-h-e,'

55:43.969 --> 55:46.923
Three years I was in
school, before my daddy,,.

55:47.014 --> 55:50.217
Sayin' God rest his soul is like
wishin' him what he had in life.

55:50.309 --> 55:53.096
He lived to rest, He was born tired.

55:53.187 --> 55:55.678
He decided,,, better use for me...

55:55.772 --> 55:59.355
than havin' me sat all day
in front of a chalkboard.

56:06.950 --> 56:12.324
Number one, lay out a winter
garden for cool-season crops.

56:12.414 --> 56:16.115
Turnips right there, onions, cabbage.

56:18.295 --> 56:19.458
Collards.

56:19.546 --> 56:23.164
Number two, patch the
shingles on the barn roof.

56:23.258 --> 56:25.547
Have we got a maul and froe?

56:25.636 --> 56:29.336
Maul? -
Maul, M-a-u-I.

56:29.431 --> 56:32.598
Number three, clear
and turn this field.

56:39.483 --> 56:43.066
No harm done lettin' it
go, Now we'll do well.

56:43.904 --> 56:44.983
Number 15,,,

56:45.072 --> 56:45.937
16,

56:46.031 --> 56:47.525
Number 16,,,
- Number 16,,.

56:47.616 --> 56:52.029
Put up some gourds for a martin
colony, Keep away these crows.

56:52.120 --> 56:57.197
One thing in abundance on this farm,
and that's crows, Shut the gate.

57:40.502 --> 57:43.207
I'd pay a dollar for an egg.

57:44.256 --> 57:46.794
I've got no quarrel with you.

57:46.884 --> 57:48.378
Hey.

57:49.386 --> 57:52.387
Am I near the Cape Fear River?

58:24.379 --> 58:27.416
Home Guard. Get back there.

58:27.508 --> 58:29.251
Runaways.

58:34.681 --> 58:36.721
Come on, boys.

58:37.893 --> 58:39.684
Let's get 'em.

58:39.770 --> 58:42.475
They're spreadin' out in the field.

58:46.693 --> 58:48.816
Come back here.
- They're in the field.

58:48.904 --> 58:51.027
They're in the field.

59:01.208 --> 59:03.497
I can get you outta here.

59:09.174 --> 59:12.211
I daresay that's Home
Guard followin' you.

59:12.302 --> 59:16.134
They're out on the road,
huntin' down deserters.

59:16.223 --> 59:18.512
And I don't recommend that way.

59:18.600 --> 59:22.468
You'll meet half the town comin'
after me with a noose, thanks to you.

59:22.563 --> 59:25.267
I should have shot you
when I had the chance.

59:25.357 --> 59:29.770
I know where there's a ferry crossin',
Or you can stubborn yourself to death,

59:31.113 --> 59:36.736
If this is a trap,,,
- Please yourself, I'm just bein' a Christian,

59:36.827 --> 59:39.400
You got any money?
- $5.

59:39.496 --> 59:43.079
For $5 I wouldn't give a parched
man a dipper of this river water.

59:43.167 --> 59:45.289
The sign says 'Ferry $5,'

59:45.377 --> 59:50.335
Nobody crosses these waters unless
they're runnin' from someplace.

59:51.258 --> 59:53.714
You wanna wait for your friends?

59:53.802 --> 59:55.961
I can give you $30 Confederate.

59:56.054 --> 59:58.380
Well, all right, let's go.

59:58.474 --> 01:00:00.431
Whatever that's worth.

01:00:05.439 --> 01:00:07.431
They cut off my hair.

01:00:08.817 --> 01:00:11.439
That was hard.

01:00:11.528 --> 01:00:13.604
I was vain about my hair.

01:00:14.406 --> 01:00:16.897
I had curls.

01:00:17.618 --> 01:00:20.369
But I deserved it.

01:00:20.454 --> 01:00:25.246
I'm the Reverend Veasey,
Have I seen you in church?

01:00:25.334 --> 01:00:28.121
No, Not likely to, neither.

