01:50:09.485 --> 01:50:11.892
Move away from the baby.

01:50:13.655 --> 01:50:15.814
Towards me.

01:50:15.908 --> 01:50:19.277
Don't shoot, We just wanted food.

01:50:19.369 --> 01:50:21.658
Take off your boots.

01:50:23.332 --> 01:50:26.701
Take off your pants,
Take off your shirt.

01:50:34.009 --> 01:50:36.085
Don't shoot me, please.

01:50:37.721 --> 01:50:41.007
We're starvin', We
haven't eaten in days,

01:50:41.099 --> 01:50:45.643
Come on,
- We're starving, We haven't eaten in days.

01:50:45.729 --> 01:50:47.805
Come on.

01:50:50.609 --> 01:50:53.147
Thanks, Thank you,

01:50:53.237 --> 01:50:55.562
Now you get runnin',
- I will,

01:50:55.656 --> 01:50:57.862
And keep runnin',
- Thank you,

01:51:58.427 --> 01:52:03.219
I love the snow,
- I hate the snow, I hate the cold,

01:52:04.850 --> 01:52:07.970
Come on.
- Fellas, what's the rush?

01:52:08.061 --> 01:52:12.558
If Ruby finds out we've spent the
night, there'll be hell to pay,

01:52:49.186 --> 01:52:52.353
'My love, where are you?

01:52:53.148 --> 01:52:56.766
'With no hope of reaching
you, I write to you,

01:52:56.860 --> 01:52:59.019
'as I always do,

01:53:00.781 --> 01:53:03.402
as I have always done.'

01:53:10.582 --> 01:53:14.960
I'm alone, but I don't worry...

01:53:15.045 --> 01:53:19.624
'Cause I'm sittin' on top of the world

01:53:23.929 --> 01:53:26.846
You reckon we could eat this?

01:53:27.599 --> 01:53:29.141
Hey.

01:53:29.226 --> 01:53:33.140
Well, you know, you cook somethin'
long enough, you can eat anything.

01:53:33.230 --> 01:53:36.266
It's froze, How long
it been there for?

01:53:36.358 --> 01:53:39.145
You hungry?
- Yeah.

01:53:39.236 --> 01:53:41.312
Not very long.

01:54:18.108 --> 01:54:19.982
Good evenin'.

01:54:20.068 --> 01:54:22.820
Hope we didn't disturb you.

01:54:22.905 --> 01:54:27.068
D'you mind if I warm
myself by your fire?

01:54:27.868 --> 01:54:29.492
Name's Teague,

01:54:29.578 --> 01:54:32.247
Do I know you?
- Stobrod Thewes,

01:54:33.457 --> 01:54:35.615
That your wife?
- That's a 'he,'

01:54:35.709 --> 01:54:37.452
Is 'he' your wife?

01:54:37.544 --> 01:54:42.123
We're musicians, He picks
a banjo, I got a fiddle.

01:54:42.216 --> 01:54:45.585
Your sweetheart's got a
nice piece of flesh on him,

01:54:45.677 --> 01:54:49.093
He looks pretty romantic by the fire,
- It's a picture of love.

01:54:55.729 --> 01:54:58.101
You gonna play that fiddle?

01:54:58.190 --> 01:54:59.850
Sure.

01:54:59.942 --> 01:55:01.899
Sure.

01:55:01.985 --> 01:55:04.061
Hey, wake up.

01:55:05.614 --> 01:55:07.654
Evenin', missis,

01:55:08.283 --> 01:55:10.953
Where's Georgia?
- 'Where's Georgia'?

01:55:15.415 --> 01:55:18.784
Captain Teague wants us to play now,
- Love to.

01:55:18.877 --> 01:55:22.709
We heard there were some deserters up
in these parts hidden out in a big cave,

01:55:22.798 --> 01:55:25.633
Not come to my ears,
- So you don't know where this big cave is?

01:55:25.717 --> 01:55:27.710
No, sir,
- You do, Stobs, He means,,.

01:55:27.803 --> 01:55:29.083
No, right, No, no.

01:55:29.179 --> 01:55:33.094
There is a cave right up near Bearpen
Branch, We played some music up there,

01:55:33.183 --> 01:55:37.762
Never occurred to me they were outliers,
- It ain't nowhere near Bearpen Branch.

01:55:37.855 --> 01:55:39.728
He's always gettin' lost.

01:55:39.815 --> 01:55:42.567
That cave
- we live there.

01:55:42.651 --> 01:55:46.980
I used to freeze up in that cave
till I got gived this new coat.

01:55:47.072 --> 01:55:51.022
Ruby made me this
coat, I like my coat.

01:55:51.118 --> 01:55:54.653
This part belonged to a reverend
and this part belonged to a horse.

01:55:54.746 --> 01:55:59.373
Ruby said - what is it? - I
should pray or neigh, dependin'.

01:55:59.459 --> 01:56:01.701
He don't,,, he don't
know what he's sayin'.

01:56:01.795 --> 01:56:05.663
He got a mind no bigger
than a pickled walnut.

01:56:05.757 --> 01:56:08.593
It's a good coat.

01:56:11.054 --> 01:56:18.433
I wish, I wish my baby was born

01:56:19.688 --> 01:56:26.984
And sittin' on its papa's knee

01:56:27.070 --> 01:56:29.110
And me, poor girl

01:56:29.198 --> 01:56:34.440
And me, poor girl, were dead and gone

01:56:35.871 --> 01:56:43.914
And the green grass
growin' o'er my feet

01:56:44.671 --> 01:56:51.919
I ain't ahead, nor never will be

01:56:53.472 --> 01:57:01.218
Till the sweet apple
grows on a sour apple tree

01:57:02.523 --> 01:57:06.935
The owl, the owl

01:57:07.027 --> 01:57:09.696
Is a lonely bird

01:57:11.448 --> 01:57:14.947
It chills my heart

01:57:15.744 --> 01:57:19.030
With dread and terror

01:57:20.165 --> 01:57:22.787
That someone's blood

01:57:22.876 --> 01:57:24.620
Someone's blood

01:57:24.711 --> 01:57:27.796
There on his wing

01:57:29.007 --> 01:57:32.590
That someone's blood

01:57:33.345 --> 01:57:37.177
There on his... feather

01:57:45.190 --> 01:57:47.064
Broke my young heart.

01:57:51.613 --> 01:57:53.606
We gonna be here all night?

01:57:56.285 --> 01:57:58.361
Stand over there.

01:58:09.423 --> 01:58:12.958
Ruby, she don't know one end
of the war from the other.

01:58:13.051 --> 01:58:16.088
You don't have to worry yourself
about her, is what I'm sayin'.

01:58:16.180 --> 01:58:19.513
Or Ada, neither, You
know what I'm sayin'?

01:58:20.142 --> 01:58:22.763
You too, You stand over there.

01:58:25.898 --> 01:58:28.223
We gonna get our tintype made?

01:58:34.907 --> 01:58:36.733
Don't smile,

01:58:36.825 --> 01:58:38.403
What?
- Quit smilin'.

01:58:38.494 --> 01:58:40.901
He always smiles, He
don't mean nothin' by it.

01:58:40.996 --> 01:58:43.569
I told him, there ain't nothin'
in this world worth a smile.

01:58:43.665 --> 01:58:46.203
Put your hat over your face.

01:58:53.008 --> 01:58:55.048
Cover your face with your hat,

01:59:03.852 --> 01:59:05.679
Ruby.
- What?

01:59:06.438 --> 01:59:07.932
Ruby.
- What's wrong?

01:59:08.023 --> 01:59:11.474
Teague,,, The Home Guard,,,
- What?

01:59:12.569 --> 01:59:14.645
They shot your daddy.

01:59:14.738 --> 01:59:16.861
They shot your daddy, and Pangle too.

01:59:22.871 --> 01:59:27.118
I told Georgia he can stop here, I
told him he can sleep in the barn.

01:59:27.209 --> 01:59:31.041
He's got nothin' inside him, He'll
walk out of here and die in the snow.

01:59:31.129 --> 01:59:34.333
He can milk the cows, I
was worried about that.

01:59:36.718 --> 01:59:40.633
It's five hours' climb
from here, He drew a map.

01:59:40.722 --> 01:59:42.715
I'm ready.

01:59:43.642 --> 01:59:47.556
You know them fools stayed
the night in the mill?

01:59:47.646 --> 01:59:51.726
That's Stobrod Thewes, Can't do one
good thing without addin' the bad.

01:59:51.817 --> 01:59:56.278
Left tracks in the snow all the
way up for the Home Guard to follow,

01:59:56.363 --> 01:59:58.688
Sign that says 'Shoot me,'
- Ruby,,.

02:00:02.035 --> 02:00:03.578
Ruby.

02:00:05.873 --> 02:00:07.912
I'm sorry.

02:00:09.918 --> 02:00:12.705
Every piece of this is man's bullshit.

02:00:12.796 --> 02:00:15.418
They call this war a
cloud over the land,

02:00:15.507 --> 02:00:20.335
but they made the weather, and then they
stand in the rain and say 'Shit, it's rainin'.'

02:00:26.185 --> 02:00:31.392
If I cry one tear for my daddy,
I stole it off a crocodile.

02:00:35.068 --> 02:00:36.148
All right, then.

02:01:25.744 --> 02:01:27.784
All right, then.

02:01:28.831 --> 02:01:31.831
Dear God.

02:01:35.963 --> 02:01:38.121
Oh, dear God.

02:01:44.388 --> 02:01:46.843
He ain't here.

02:01:46.932 --> 02:01:50.799
Agh. Teague's probably took him.

02:01:50.894 --> 02:01:54.762
They did that with the
Swanger boys, didn't they?

02:01:54.857 --> 02:01:57.893
Strung 'em up, as a warnin'.

02:02:03.115 --> 02:02:05.357
They took his coat.

02:02:05.450 --> 02:02:07.324
Why would they take his coat?

02:02:12.916 --> 02:02:16.083
Daddy? Daddy.

02:02:16.170 --> 02:02:18.127
Daddy.

02:02:24.136 --> 02:02:25.334
Daddy?

02:02:25.429 --> 02:02:28.002
He's still breathin'.

02:02:28.098 --> 02:02:30.720
It's Ruby.

02:02:30.809 --> 02:02:32.553
Don't you die on me again.

02:02:38.650 --> 02:02:42.862
We gotta get him home,
- He won't make it, He'll die first.

02:02:42.946 --> 02:02:46.362
He's got hardly no blood left in him.

02:02:49.161 --> 02:02:51.070
There it is, I feel it,

02:02:51.163 --> 02:02:52.242
You got it?
- Yep.

02:02:53.123 --> 02:02:57.584
There's a place close. Old
Cherokee, it used to be.

02:02:57.669 --> 02:03:00.160
It's got shelter, water.

02:03:00.255 --> 02:03:02.877
I used to hide up there
when he'd get a temper goin'.

02:03:02.966 --> 02:03:04.923
God.

02:03:12.267 --> 02:03:16.395
I'll go look for some food,
- Take the shotgun.

02:03:42.339 --> 02:03:43.999
Goddamn.

02:03:54.810 --> 02:03:56.886
Turn around.

02:03:58.397 --> 02:04:01.018
Go back where you came from.

02:04:02.568 --> 02:04:04.940
Go back.

02:04:08.407 --> 02:04:10.483
Ada?

02:04:11.243 --> 02:04:12.406
Ada Monroe?

02:04:14.371 --> 02:04:17.158
Turn around or I'll shoot.

02:04:45.652 --> 02:04:47.147
Inman?

02:04:47.237 --> 02:04:49.313
Inman?

02:05:02.503 --> 02:05:04.709
Inman.

02:05:36.829 --> 02:05:39.117
You better come with me.

02:05:51.468 --> 02:05:53.544
Ruby.

02:05:54.471 --> 02:05:56.049
This is Inman.

02:06:01.228 --> 02:06:03.600
Oh. Congratulations.

02:06:03.689 --> 02:06:07.224
Oughta send you out with
a shotgun a lot more.

02:06:08.986 --> 02:06:12.152
Looks if he's about to topple over,

02:06:12.239 --> 02:06:14.860
I may need to,
- You shot or somethin'?

02:06:16.869 --> 02:06:18.446
Not lately,

02:06:29.840 --> 02:06:33.007
He's asleep,
- I ain't surprised,

02:06:33.093 --> 02:06:37.257
Your man looked tuckered out,
- I saw him.

02:06:37.347 --> 02:06:41.760
In Sally Swanger's well, A man
like a black smudge in the snow,

02:06:41.852 --> 02:06:44.888
Well, there you go,
- It wasn't the same, what I saw.

02:06:44.980 --> 02:06:47.186
In the well it was
as if he were falling,

02:06:47.274 --> 02:06:50.939
You probably just don't remember it right,
- I remember it exactly.

02:06:51.028 --> 02:06:53.234
There were crows - black crows.

02:06:53.322 --> 02:06:55.445
They were flyin' towards me.

02:06:55.532 --> 02:06:58.984
Ruby, I thought I was seein' him fall.

02:07:01.246 --> 02:07:04.331
Instead, I was seein'
him come back to me.

02:07:06.835 --> 02:07:10.169
I got big plans for that farm.

02:07:14.176 --> 02:07:16.881
I know.

02:07:16.970 --> 02:07:18.762
I know you have.

02:07:18.847 --> 02:07:22.762
I got a vision in my mind
of how Black Cove oughta be.

02:07:26.897 --> 02:07:29.186
I don't know, Ruby.

02:07:29.274 --> 02:07:33.568
All this while I've been
packin' ice around my heart.

02:07:36.114 --> 02:07:38.950
How do I make it melt?

02:07:41.912 --> 02:07:43.371
Hey.

02:07:44.456 --> 02:07:47.291
You about done with my knife?

02:07:47.376 --> 02:07:50.081
We got a bird to cook.

02:07:50.170 --> 02:07:51.962
Just about.

02:07:54.883 --> 02:07:58.667
You're makin' a pig's ear of that job.

02:08:00.139 --> 02:08:02.215
Give it to me.

02:08:08.063 --> 02:08:10.850
Oh, I ain't gonna cut you.

02:08:12.526 --> 02:08:16.737
Can't see that it'd make a
bit of difference if I did.

02:08:27.541 --> 02:08:29.747
You got the right feelings for her?

02:08:29.835 --> 02:08:33.085
Don't turn your head. Tsk.

02:08:36.842 --> 02:08:38.170
I do.

02:09:03.744 --> 02:09:07.279
I'm sorry, I was tryin' to be quiet.

02:09:12.961 --> 02:09:15.333
Did you get my letters?

02:09:17.007 --> 02:09:19.165
I got three letters.

02:09:19.968 --> 02:09:24.761
I carried them, I carried
them in the book you gave me.

02:09:24.848 --> 02:09:26.307
The Bartram.

02:09:27.476 --> 02:09:30.892
I probably sent 103.

02:09:35.567 --> 02:09:38.141
Did you write to me?

02:09:38.237 --> 02:09:40.146
Whenever I could.

02:09:40.239 --> 02:09:42.445
If you never got
them, I can summarize,

02:09:42.533 --> 02:09:45.368
No, No, no,
- 'I pray you are well,

02:09:45.452 --> 02:09:47.741
'I pray I am in your thoughts.

02:09:47.830 --> 02:09:53.072
You are all that keeps me from
slidin' into some dark place,'

02:09:53.168 --> 02:09:56.253
How did I keep you?

02:09:56.338 --> 02:09:59.209
We barely knew each other,
It was a few moments.

02:09:59.299 --> 02:10:01.209
A thousand moments.

02:10:04.012 --> 02:10:07.678
They're like a bag,,
, of tiny diamonds.

02:10:09.101 --> 02:10:12.719
Don't matter if they're
real or things I made up.

02:10:14.898 --> 02:10:17.105
The shape of your neck.

02:10:18.986 --> 02:10:21.441
That's real.

02:10:21.530 --> 02:10:25.658
The way you felt under my
hands when I pulled you to me.

02:10:36.920 --> 02:10:39.625
You were ploughing a field.

02:10:40.591 --> 02:10:43.129
You were carrying a tray,

02:10:43.218 --> 02:10:46.005
You wouldn't come in,
- No, I wouldn't go in.

02:10:46.096 --> 02:10:51.007
So that's why I had to carry a
tray, So I could come out to see you.

02:10:53.103 --> 02:10:56.187
That kiss.

02:10:56.273 --> 02:10:59.891
Which I kissed every
day of my walking.

02:11:01.612 --> 02:11:03.735
Every day I was waiting.

02:11:04.615 --> 02:11:06.025
Longing.

02:11:06.116 --> 02:11:09.200
Longing to see your face.

02:11:15.417 --> 02:11:18.667
If you could see my inside,,.

02:11:18.754 --> 02:11:23.748
Now, whatever you wanna name it
- my spirit? That's what I fear.

02:11:24.801 --> 02:11:26.759
I think I'm ruined.

02:11:26.845 --> 02:11:30.345
They kept tryin' to
put me in the ground,

02:11:31.600 --> 02:11:34.269
But I wasn't ready,
- Inman,,.

02:11:34.353 --> 02:11:37.769
But if I had,,, if I
had goodness, I lost it.

02:11:39.983 --> 02:11:43.233
If I had anything tender
in me, I shot it dead.

02:11:44.905 --> 02:11:48.772
How could I write to
you after what I done,

02:11:49.743 --> 02:11:50.822
what I seen?

02:11:50.911 --> 02:11:52.405
Number one,

02:11:52.496 --> 02:11:54.821
shut this door, It's freezin'.

02:11:54.915 --> 02:11:57.916
Number two, shut that
door, It's freezin'.

02:11:58.001 --> 02:12:00.457
Layin' on my back, my
fingers poked in my ears,

02:12:00.546 --> 02:12:03.250
tryin' to shut out who's
got a bag of diamonds,

02:12:03.340 --> 02:12:05.629
who's carrying a tray,,.

02:12:05.717 --> 02:12:08.090
If you wanna get three
feet up a bull's ass,

02:12:08.178 --> 02:12:11.713
just listen to what sweethearts
whisper to one another.

02:12:11.807 --> 02:12:17.477
In fact, if y'all gonna wimble-wimble
all night, I'm gonna sleep in with him,

02:12:32.286 --> 02:12:35.121
I'll say good night,
- No.

02:12:38.500 --> 02:12:40.576
Please,,,

02:12:41.587 --> 02:12:43.247
don't say good night.

02:13:08.071 --> 02:13:10.859
Wars make some things pointless.

02:13:15.037 --> 02:13:17.409
It's hard to imagine a wedding.

02:13:19.625 --> 02:13:22.994
I think even my father
would recognize that.

02:13:23.670 --> 02:13:25.746
Ada, I wanna marry you.

02:13:27.466 --> 02:13:29.708
If you'll have me.

02:13:30.469 --> 02:13:35.345
Isn't there some religion where you just
have to say 'I marry you' three times,

02:13:35.432 --> 02:13:37.425
and you're man and wife?

02:13:38.393 --> 02:13:40.433
I marry you.

02:13:41.522 --> 02:13:43.728
I marry you, I marry you.

02:13:48.821 --> 02:13:50.860
Why is that funny?

02:13:50.948 --> 02:13:55.574
I think it's 'I divorce you' three
times and you're not married anymore.

02:13:57.579 --> 02:13:58.990
I can wait for you.

02:13:59.623 --> 02:14:05.044
Oh, Inman, I marry you,
I marry you, I marry you.

02:14:05.128 --> 02:14:07.121
I marry you, I marry you.

02:14:14.972 --> 02:14:18.720
I have so,,, I have
so many buttons, Sorry.

02:14:22.437 --> 02:14:25.225
Will you turn your back?

02:14:36.451 --> 02:14:37.827
No.

02:14:40.122 --> 02:14:42.411
No, I will not.

02:16:27.521 --> 02:16:30.438
I'll lead the horse at a
pace your daddy can tolerate,

02:16:30.524 --> 02:16:34.189
You two go ahead now,
- No, I don't wanna do that,

02:16:34.278 --> 02:16:37.029
No, We can all go together,
- It's safer this way.

02:16:37.114 --> 02:16:39.439
We're deserters, No one
has a quarrel with you.

02:16:39.532 --> 02:16:41.691
He's right.

02:16:41.785 --> 02:16:45.735
I gather I,,, I need
permission from you, Ruby,

02:16:45.831 --> 02:16:49.164
if I reckon on livin' at Black Cove.

02:16:58.343 --> 02:16:59.968
All right, then.

02:17:03.932 --> 02:17:06.008
You stay on that horse.

02:17:06.101 --> 02:17:09.138
And don't lose it, Or sell it.

02:17:09.938 --> 02:17:12.808
Gonna need it back on the farm.

02:17:15.777 --> 02:17:17.853
All right, Daddy.

02:17:21.992 --> 02:17:24.565
I don't wanna let you go.

02:17:27.371 --> 02:17:29.780
I'll be with you by nightfall.

02:17:35.464 --> 02:17:36.839
Ugh.

02:17:38.799 --> 02:17:40.877
All right, then.

02:18:11.708 --> 02:18:15.540
Hope that Georgia boy's
been tendin' to the animals,

02:18:15.629 --> 02:18:18.500
I knew you were thinkin' on him,
- I was not.

02:18:18.590 --> 02:18:20.998
I was thinkin' on swollen udders,
- Oh,,,.

02:18:21.093 --> 02:18:25.340
And before you say 'same difference',,,
- I'm sayin' nothin'.

02:18:25.430 --> 02:18:29.891
Miss Lovey-Dovey.
Miss Lovey-Dovey.

02:18:29.977 --> 02:18:32.016
Hey.

02:18:32.103 --> 02:18:36.232
That was a long funeral for your daddy,
- That was a wake.

02:18:36.316 --> 02:18:37.941
That was Irish.

02:18:39.986 --> 02:18:41.896
Now, your friend Georgia here,,.

02:18:41.989 --> 02:18:45.607
We went down to visit you when we
heard you were harbourin' deserters,

02:18:45.700 --> 02:18:49.829
and he told us - after some
persuasion - you were up here.

02:18:49.913 --> 02:18:52.784
We were up and down this mountain.

02:18:52.875 --> 02:18:54.665
Up and down.

02:18:54.751 --> 02:18:56.577
There will be a reckoning.

02:18:56.670 --> 02:18:59.706
When this war is over,
there will be a reckoning.

02:19:01.424 --> 02:19:03.501
Did you make this coat?

02:19:03.593 --> 02:19:05.585
Helpin' a deserter
- that's treason.

02:19:05.679 --> 02:19:10.258
Now, I know it's half
horse and half reverend.

02:19:11.894 --> 02:19:13.851
A reckonin'?

02:19:15.439 --> 02:19:18.938
The reckoning's for your world.

02:19:19.026 --> 02:19:21.647
It's not mine.

02:19:25.031 --> 02:19:28.448
I'll'llbe damned, He's
a hard bastard to kill,

02:19:30.870 --> 02:19:33.325
No.
- Ruby.

02:19:40.172 --> 02:19:41.714
Inman.

02:19:55.395 --> 02:19:57.222
Captain Teague.

02:20:39.356 --> 02:20:43.306
Come down from there.
- No, sir, Here is fine.

02:20:43.402 --> 02:20:46.356
I'll just shoot the
horse out from under you,

02:20:46.446 --> 02:20:49.613
You ridin' Captain Teague's animal?
- I am,

02:20:49.700 --> 02:20:52.820
He dead?
- I hope so.

02:20:52.911 --> 02:20:57.289
Look, give me your gun and ride on
home, I'm done fightin', I'm sick of it.

02:20:57.374 --> 02:20:59.947
I give you my gun, you're
gonna shoot me dead.

02:21:00.043 --> 02:21:02.499
I will not shoot you, but nor
am I goin' down this mountain...

02:21:02.588 --> 02:21:04.746
lookin' over my shoulder for you.

02:21:04.840 --> 02:21:07.129
That's what they call a conundrum,

02:21:11.638 --> 02:21:15.636
I'll tell you what I got on my side,
- What you got on your side?

02:21:22.566 --> 02:21:24.274
The confidence of youth.

02:21:39.666 --> 02:21:41.825
Inman.

02:22:33.178 --> 02:22:35.254
No.

02:23:10.924 --> 02:23:12.122
I,,,

02:23:13.177 --> 02:23:15.668
came,,, back.

02:23:24.563 --> 02:23:26.639
I love you.

02:24:00.140 --> 02:24:02.347
Baby.

02:24:28.085 --> 02:24:32.830
What we have lost will
never be returned to us.

02:24:32.923 --> 02:24:36.007
The land will not heal.

02:24:36.093 --> 02:24:39.047
Too much blood.

02:24:39.138 --> 02:24:42.838
The heart will not heal.

02:24:42.933 --> 02:24:46.634
All we can do is make
peace with the past...

02:24:46.728 --> 02:24:49.184
and try to learn from it.

02:24:52.317 --> 02:24:56.647
What are you doing?
- He died in the night, love.

02:24:57.990 --> 02:24:59.899
Bring him here,

02:24:59.992 --> 02:25:03.158
Don't kill him,
- I'm not gonna kill him.

02:25:03.245 --> 02:25:07.195
We have to try somethin'
or else he's gonna die too.

02:25:07.291 --> 02:25:09.414
It's all right.

02:25:10.878 --> 02:25:13.748
We're gonna try a little trick.

02:25:13.839 --> 02:25:16.294
Shh.

02:25:35.402 --> 02:25:39.649
There are days now when I
manage not to think of you.

02:25:40.908 --> 02:25:46.068
When the needs of the farm call
with more urgency than my heart.

02:25:47.748 --> 02:25:51.746
This time of year there's
so much life everywhere.

02:25:53.629 --> 02:25:56.250
I find you in all of it.

02:25:57.716 --> 02:26:01.334
As if you were still
walking home to me.

02:26:03.764 --> 02:26:07.844
If you could see us now this
Easter day at Black Cove,

02:26:07.935 --> 02:26:11.517
you would know every step
of your journey was worth it.

02:26:11.605 --> 02:26:15.306
I'm still climbing upwards

02:26:15.400 --> 02:26:18.686
And my journey's almost ended

02:26:18.779 --> 02:26:22.112
So, friend, if you're thirsty

02:26:22.199 --> 02:26:25.698
Climb this mountain with me

02:26:28.831 --> 02:26:32.200
Grace Inman, nobody said 'Eat,'

02:26:45.013 --> 02:26:49.759
For good friends,
good food, good family,

02:26:49.852 --> 02:26:52.852
all our blessings, O
Lord, we thank thee,

02:26:52.938 --> 02:26:54.397
Amen,
- Amen,

02:26:54.481 --> 02:26:56.141
Amen,
- Amen.

02:26:56.233 --> 02:26:58.771
Amen.

02:26:58.861 --> 02:27:02.561
Sweetheart, there's no cider,
- That's for you.

02:27:02.656 --> 02:27:07.152
Right, I'd best,,, I'd best
fetch it, I got my orders.

02:27:10.080 --> 02:27:13.864
I looked once more down Sally's well,

02:27:13.959 --> 02:27:17.577
and this time there was
nothin' there to haunt me.

02:27:19.047 --> 02:27:21.005
Just clouds.

02:27:21.091 --> 02:27:25.468
Clouds, and then... sun.

02:29:32.473 --> 02:29:38.012
Well I recall his parting words

02:29:38.103 --> 02:29:42.979
Must I accept his fate

02:29:43.066 --> 02:29:48.772
Or take myself far from this place?

02:29:48.864 --> 02:29:54.534
I thought I heard a black bell toll

02:29:54.620 --> 02:29:59.246
A little bird did sing

02:29:59.333 --> 02:30:02.037
Man has no choice

02:30:02.127 --> 02:30:06.456
When he wants every thing

02:30:08.550 --> 02:30:14.221
We'll rise above the scarlet tide

02:30:14.306 --> 02:30:20.012
That trickles down
through the mountain

02:30:20.103 --> 02:30:27.649
And separates the widow from the bride

02:30:35.244 --> 02:30:40.867
Man goes beyond his own decision

02:30:40.958 --> 02:30:46.581
Gets caught up in the mechanism

02:30:46.672 --> 02:30:52.342
Of swindlers who act like kings

02:30:52.427 --> 02:30:58.264
And brokers who break everything

02:30:58.350 --> 02:31:04.020
The dark of night was swiftly fading

02:31:04.106 --> 02:31:05.897
Close to the dawn of day

02:31:08.944 --> 02:31:15.148
Why would I want him
just to lose him again?

02:31:17.578 --> 02:31:23.248
We'll rise above the scarlet tide

02:31:23.333 --> 02:31:29.039
That trickles down
through the mountain

02:31:29.131 --> 02:31:36.462
And separates the widow from the bride

02:31:56.742 --> 02:32:02.578
You'll walk unscathed
through musket fire

02:32:03.916 --> 02:32:09.835
No ploughman's blade
will cut thee down

02:32:11.298 --> 02:32:17.467
No cutler's horn will mark thy face

02:32:17.554 --> 02:32:23.924
And you will be my ain true love

02:32:24.019 --> 02:32:29.939
And you will be my ain true love

02:32:32.528 --> 02:32:38.400
And as you walk through
death's dark veil

02:32:39.535 --> 02:32:44.909
The cannon's thunder can't prevail

02:32:46.208 --> 02:32:51.831
And those who hunt thee down will fail

02:32:52.673 --> 02:32:58.545
And you will be my ain true love

02:32:59.555 --> 02:33:05.593
And you will be my ain true love

02:33:08.021 --> 02:33:14.190
Asleep inside the cannon's mouth

02:33:15.154 --> 02:33:20.859
The captain cries
'Here comes the rout'

02:33:21.785 --> 02:33:27.740
They'll seek to find
me north and south

02:33:27.833 --> 02:33:34.085
I've gone to find my ain true love

02:33:36.425 --> 02:33:42.926
The field is cut and bleeds to red

02:33:43.015 --> 02:33:48.768
The cannonballs fly round my head

02:33:49.688 --> 02:33:56.141
The infirmary man may count me dead

02:33:56.236 --> 02:34:02.488
When I've gone to
find my ain true love

